Office of the Osun State governor, Rauf Aregbesola, was on Monday gutted by fire. According to an eyewitness, the fire started around 4 pm and was devastating as the security doors leading to the office could not be opened as it raged. Firefighters have put off the fire and the office was cordoned off by security men. Special Adviser to the Governor on Media, Mr Sola Fasure said the investigation has commenced on the incident. Details later. To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .